CNCP v1 25020
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5920: problem with `reactive` handling objects with inner properties that are classes",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:19.050900+00:00",
  "text": "problem with `reactive` handling objects with inner properties that are classes\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIt is self-contained in the provided the SFC Playground reproduction\n\n### What is expected?\n\nIt is expected that \r\n\r\n`const test: ITest = reactive<ITest>(testObj);`\r\n\r\nworks properly in regard to type matching.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nI get an error from the TypeScript language server in VSC. \r\n\r\nTypeScript types matching with `reactive` are not handling properly classes. It reduces them to empty objects `{}`\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\r\n    OS: macOS 11.4\r\n    CPU: (8) x64 Apple M1\r\n    Memory: 21.72 MB / 16.00 GB\r\n    Shell: 5.8 - /bin/zsh\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 16.13.0 - /usr/local/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.5 - ~/.yarn/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 8.1.0 - /usr/local/bin/npm\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 101.0.4951.64\r\n    Chrome Canary: 104.0.5061.0\r\n    Edge: 96.0.1054.62\r\n    Firefox: 99.0\r\n    Safari: 14.1.1\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    vue: ^3.2.33 => 3.2.33\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIf this is a technical limitation and we have to do some workarounds it should be mentioned in [reactive doc](https://vuejs.org/api/reactivity-core.html#reactive) but there is no mention.\r\n\r\nI can imagine we should use interfaces instead of classes but again, it would be a serious drawback for various use-cases.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: reactivity",
    "scope: types"
  ],
